Python Syntax

- After a colon (:), the next line must be indented (usually 4 spaces).
- All lines in the same block use the same indentation.
- One simple statement per line is normal; semicolons can chain statements but are rarely used.

Common mistakes (these will cause IndentationError or SyntaxError if written as real code):
- Forgetting to indent under if / for / def / class.
- Mixing tabs and spaces.
- Wrong indent level for a second line in the same block.

Run syntax.py for valid examples. See statement.py for multiple prints on one line.

See also: https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_syntax.asp

